Post subject: Lady Vox<br>
<br>
Another note which most raids ignore for some reason. ALL tanks except rogues should be at her front. Even monks and rangers. All of them as one in front. They will push her so badly her complete heals get interrupted. This is the single most effective way to stop an unstunnable from CHing... push it.<br>
<br>
I did a raid with 30 people, only 2 chanters. One got feared from the first roar, and the other was summoned after her first sieve and killed. Vox didn't CH even one time. She TRIED twice, but interrupted the first time, interrupted the second time, then died. I've never seen her owned so badly. One person died... the summoned chanter.<br>
<br>
Outside of that, seive from a distance, it helps with aggro. If you manage to land 3 seives with 2 other chanters doing the same, she will likely not get more than 1 CH off. If she gets a CH off don't panic, just do your job, and rune your clerics.<br>
<br>
You will be summoned to your death after runing a cleric--fact 9/10 times.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
(addendum)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.crimsontalon.com/raidvox.htm">www.crimsontalon.com/raidvox.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
 9. A major key to killing Vox is to not push her onto a wall. IF VOX GETS PUSHED ONTO A WALL SHE WILL STAND THERE, HEAL HERSELF, AND SUMMON PEOPLE. Those that are between Vox and the nearest wall should not taunt. If you are near the wall and are the current agro, move away from the wall.<br>
<br>
<br>
(It would seem then, that the idea would be to continuously push her around, but make certain she is never pushed onto a wall.)<br>
<br>
<br>
stephenmcleod<br>
<br>
Post subject: Lady Vox <br>
<br>
3) you will be buffing and seiving. Your sieving is CRITICAL. SO don't let them strip you of mana buffing and then start the raid before you have mana.<br>
<br>
<br>
(#4 is an interesting, and possibly life saving, tip if true. Can anyone verify or dispute this?)<br>
<br>
<br>
4) Do not have levitation on. If feared you will path into the pits if levitated. You will not fear into the pits of you are not levitated.<br>
<br>
5) get a GOOD map (eqatlas is good) and drop tiny daggers at the edges of the tunnels leading to pits before you start. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umoxxibixiebane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moxxi Bixiebane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/14/02 6:11:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=84.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Open Raid of Lady Vox Saturday the 14th 1pm NOON EST</span><hr size=1> 52 warrior reporting in /salute.<br>
